<h1 style="color:lightblue"; align="center">Photosynthesis</h1>
<div class="mystyle";>Plants are unique and essential in our environment, and their distinctivity 
                      comes from the process called photosynthesis. Photosynthesis is a process in which 
                      autotrophs convert water, carbon dioxide, and sunlight into glucose and other    
                      beneficial molecules. More precisely, the equation for photosynthesis is
                      6H<sub>2</sub>O + 6CO<sub>2</sub> + sunlight to C<sub>6</sub>O<sub>12</sub>H<sub>6</sub> + O2. There are two types of
                     photosynthesis, <b> light dependent and light independent </b>. Light dependent reactions
                     occur when plants have access to sunlight to produce energy called <b>ATP</b>
                    (Adenosine Triphosphate). However, light independent reactions don't require
                    sunlight to partake in photosynthesis, thus it can occur both during the day or night.
    <h1 align="center"> Importance of Photosynthesis</h1>
    <p>Photosynthesis is essential in life because photosynthesis provides products that humans use, oxygen. Cellular respiration requires oxygen to act as the final electron acceptor, and plants provide 
        that quality element. On the other spectrum, plants also need CO<sub>2</sub> to undergo photosynthesis. The glucose, produced in photosynthesis, is also beneficial to humans as humans consume glucose.
        The work the plants do is essential for the environement as different organisms utilze the oxygen.<br>
         <h1 style="text-align: center" class="mystyle";> </h>
